1
00:00:01,168 --> 00:00:03,544
Oh, crap, crap, crap.

2
00:00:03,545 --> 00:00:05,379
The aquarium is not gonna be
open in time for our field trip.

3
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:06,923
I still can't believe
people really thought

4
00:00:06,924 --> 00:00:09,634
it was a good idea to free
the fish after the Super Bowl.

5
00:00:09,635 --> 00:00:11,093
Eagles fans
are really, uh...

6
00:00:11,094 --> 00:00:12,637
What?

7
00:00:12,638 --> 00:00:14,680
Unique.

8
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:17,225
So does this mean no
end-of-the-year field trip?

9
00:00:17,226 --> 00:00:19,227
Oh, no.
There will be a field trip.

10
00:00:19,228 --> 00:00:21,020
I've learned to book
a backup just in case.

11
00:00:21,021 --> 00:00:22,605
So we will be
going to...

12
00:00:22,606 --> 00:00:24,565
Broadway!
A Broadway show!

13
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:27,443
No.
That's a good idea.

14
00:00:27,444 --> 00:00:29,111
New York's not far.
I'll save that for next time.

15
00:00:29,112 --> 00:00:31,948
No, we are going to
the Please Touch Museum.

16
00:00:31,949 --> 00:00:34,825
Ooh, fantastic.

17
00:00:34,826 --> 00:00:36,452
And maybe they
will find the shark

18
00:00:36,453 --> 00:00:38,412
and we get to see him
next year at the aquarium.

19
00:00:38,413 --> 00:00:40,081
Exactly.
Mr. Johnson:
Good morning, y'all.

20
00:00:40,082 --> 00:00:42,291
Morning.
Does anyone need
shark fin soup?

21
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:45,253
My freezer is stuffed
to the gills with it.

22
00:00:45,254 --> 00:00:47,630
Shark is the tuna
of the sea.

23
00:00:47,631 --> 00:00:50,633
[ Maker's "Hold'em" playing ]

24
00:00:50,634 --> 00:00:53,636
-- Captions by Verbit--

25
00:00:53,637 --> 00:00:59,059
♪

26
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:04,063
[ Gasps ] I just bought
a cute little outfit like that

27
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:05,523
for my future
glamchild.

28
00:01:05,524 --> 00:01:07,358
You look like you're about
to take me to court

29
00:01:07,359 --> 00:01:08,901
for stealing your Binky.

30
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:11,112
Look, I feel the need
to kindly remind you

31
00:01:11,113 --> 00:01:13,573
to never put baby
in a corner.

32
00:01:13,574 --> 00:01:15,491
Today we are going
to the district

33
00:01:15,492 --> 00:01:17,868
to make a formal appeal
to get Ava her job back.

34
00:01:17,869 --> 00:01:21,622
The disciplinary board is giving
us a chance to plead our case.

35
00:01:21,623 --> 00:01:24,166
Jacob watched four seasons
of "Law & Order" to prepare.

36
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:26,836
I watched "Shogun,"
which didn't help,

37
00:01:26,837 --> 00:01:29,672
but I do know a lot
about seppuku.

38
00:01:29,673 --> 00:01:31,424
I don't like it.

39
00:01:31,425 --> 00:01:33,926
So it took a miracle,
but I managed to get a few subs

40
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:35,469
to cover all your classes
for the rest of the day,

41
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:36,637
so don't worry
about rushing back.

42
00:01:36,638 --> 00:01:37,805
Good, good, good.

43
00:01:37,806 --> 00:01:39,098
Good morning,
Principal Eddie.

44
00:01:39,099 --> 00:01:40,641
Oh, good morning,
Langston.

45
00:01:40,642 --> 00:01:42,852
Now hurry up and get to class
before the bell rings.

46
00:01:42,853 --> 00:01:43,936
Alright, good luck, y'all.

47
00:01:43,937 --> 00:01:45,771
Alright,
I'll see you two there.

48
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:47,440
Wait. No, no, I thought we were
all gonna ride together.

49
00:01:47,441 --> 00:01:49,900
Yeah, I made
a "Rollin' With the Homies"

50
00:01:49,901 --> 00:01:50,901
playlist
for the commute.

51
00:01:50,902 --> 00:01:52,403
Sweet Cheeks' car seat

52
00:01:52,404 --> 00:01:54,405
takes up, like,
my entire back seat, so...

53
00:01:54,406 --> 00:01:57,450
And I'm just gonna ride
with her because...

54
00:01:57,451 --> 00:01:59,452
I don't want to hear
that playlist.

55
00:01:59,453 --> 00:02:02,288
Uh--
Let's go get a job back,
young people.

56
00:02:02,289 --> 00:02:04,790
Come on.
Okay, I really think
we should take one car.

57
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:05,791
You guys, the planet.

58
00:02:05,792 --> 00:02:07,626
And as you can see,

59
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:10,129
I was only trying to do what was
best for our staff and students.

60
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:12,131
So you didn't extort
a local business

61
00:02:12,132 --> 00:02:15,343
and accept contributions
that go against district policy?

62
00:02:15,344 --> 00:02:17,511
No, I did, because
that was what was best

63
00:02:17,512 --> 00:02:18,804
for our staff
and students.

64
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:20,348
May I approach the table
as a character witness?

65
00:02:20,349 --> 00:02:22,850
Just stay
where you are.

66
00:02:22,851 --> 00:02:27,438
Look, we can-- we can discuss
"the facts" or "what happened"

67
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:29,523
all day until we're
blue in the face.

68
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:30,567
You know?

69
00:02:35,113 --> 00:02:37,490
Um, let me try.
Yeah.

70
00:02:37,491 --> 00:02:41,535
Ladies and gentlemen,
it is safe to assume

71
00:02:41,536 --> 00:02:45,539
that we are all
God-fearing people, is it not?

72
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:46,957
No, not at all.

73
00:02:46,958 --> 00:02:48,167
Why would you
assume that?

74
00:02:48,168 --> 00:02:50,669
I'm, like, spiritual
when I need to be.

75
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:52,505
Oh, my, my, my.

76
00:02:52,506 --> 00:02:53,756
[ Chuckles ]

77
00:02:53,757 --> 00:02:55,132
Janine:
Ava only bent the rules

78
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:57,093
because we have so little
at Abbott.

79
00:02:57,094 --> 00:02:58,803
Melissa:
Little? Try nothing.

80
00:02:58,804 --> 00:03:01,514
There are public parks
with more resources than us.

81
00:03:01,515 --> 00:03:03,140
You want us to come
to your house

82
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:04,433
and take
your toilet paper?

83
00:03:04,434 --> 00:03:05,559
That felt like a threat.

84
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,852
I would like to declare
Miss Schemmenti

85
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:08,604
a hostile witness.
What?

86
00:03:08,605 --> 00:03:10,689
Listen, if I'm accused
of doing whatever it takes

87
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:12,483
to help our kids,
then guilty as charged.

88
00:03:12,484 --> 00:03:14,026
Yes,
is caring too much

89
00:03:14,027 --> 00:03:15,361
something you really
want to punish?

90
00:03:15,362 --> 00:03:17,279
Barbara:
Ava is an amazing principal,

91
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:19,156
and she has more than
learned her lesson.

92
00:03:19,157 --> 00:03:21,784
And is that really what you want
to say to the educators

93
00:03:21,785 --> 00:03:23,744
of the Philadelphia
public school system?

94
00:03:23,745 --> 00:03:24,995
Care less?

95
00:03:24,996 --> 00:03:27,039
It's powerful testimony.

96
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,833
Just give us a second.

97
00:03:28,834 --> 00:03:30,543
[ Sighs ]
Okay.

98
00:03:30,544 --> 00:03:32,837
[ Indistinct conversation ]

99
00:03:32,838 --> 00:03:34,463
Appeal denied.

100
00:03:34,464 --> 00:03:37,800
Ms. Coleman is still fired
for lying to the board.

101
00:03:37,801 --> 00:03:39,218
Wait.
There is one thing.

102
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:40,302
Yes?

103
00:03:40,303 --> 00:03:42,138
Pay for your parking
at the machine

104
00:03:42,139 --> 00:03:44,014
before you
get to your car.

105
00:03:44,015 --> 00:03:45,599
People don't like
being held up at the gate

106
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,184
while you're fumbling
for your credit card.

107
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:48,727
Okay. Bye.

108
00:03:48,728 --> 00:03:50,479
Wait, wait, wait.

109
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:54,859
Um... we have some new
smoking-gun evidence

110
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:57,445
that we'd like a few minutes
to review

111
00:03:57,446 --> 00:04:00,156
and bring it
to your honors,

112
00:04:00,157 --> 00:04:01,740
your honors, please.
Yes, yes.

113
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:04,118
Okay.

114
00:04:04,119 --> 00:04:06,537
Set a timer
for 30 seconds.

115
00:04:06,538 --> 00:04:07,746
Oh, my God. Okay.
Melissa: Come on, guys.

116
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:09,540
I would have
given them 15.

117
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:10,541
Well, I'm hungry.

118
00:04:10,542 --> 00:04:12,543
Oh, God,
I love surprise evidence.

119
00:04:12,544 --> 00:04:14,253
What do you got?
I got nothing.
I was stalling.

120
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:16,714
What?
I told you, they're not
backing down from this.

121
00:04:16,715 --> 00:04:18,174
This is so unfair!

122
00:04:18,175 --> 00:04:19,675
Why couldn't they
take me instead?

123
00:04:19,676 --> 00:04:21,469
Oh, my God,
they told us during the audit

124
00:04:21,470 --> 00:04:23,095
that it's really hard
to fire teachers.

125
00:04:23,096 --> 00:04:25,139
And with the sub shortage,
they can't suspend all of us.

126
00:04:25,140 --> 00:04:27,391
So what if we go in there,
admit it was us,

127
00:04:27,392 --> 00:04:28,976
and-- and we'll get
a slap on the wrist,

128
00:04:28,977 --> 00:04:29,894
and then Ava
gets her job back.

129
00:04:29,895 --> 00:04:31,645
A sacrifice.

130
00:04:31,646 --> 00:04:34,231
Oh, Barbara Howard the Martyr
does have a nice ring to it.

131
00:04:34,232 --> 00:04:36,233
Uh, to be clear,
you all did do it.

132
00:04:36,234 --> 00:04:38,110
You initiated the bribing.
I'm a hero.

133
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:39,904
[ Thud ]
Oh, my God.

134
00:04:39,905 --> 00:04:41,739
Okay,
so are we doing this?

135
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:44,116
Pleading guilty to anything is
against everything I stand for.

136
00:04:44,117 --> 00:04:45,326
So we'll call it
no contest.

137
00:04:45,327 --> 00:04:46,619
Let's go!
Melissa: Okay.

138
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:48,954
Whoo! I am vibrating
with adrenaline.

139
00:04:48,955 --> 00:04:50,748
Is this what it feels like
to play a team sport?

140
00:04:50,749 --> 00:04:52,500
Y'all are so embarrassing.

141
00:04:52,501 --> 00:04:53,543
Thank you.

142
00:04:55,086 --> 00:04:57,046
Miles, thank you for stopping by
on short notice.

143
00:04:57,047 --> 00:04:58,380
Please, sign in.

144
00:04:58,381 --> 00:04:59,632
Looks like
somebody benefited

145
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:02,176
from the little shake-up
around here, huh?

146
00:05:02,177 --> 00:05:05,262
Um, yeah.
Please, come to my office.

147
00:05:05,263 --> 00:05:07,181
Okay, well...

148
00:05:07,182 --> 00:05:09,725
I know we lost the things that
we got from the golf course,

149
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:12,645
but I was hoping that I could
save the students' golf <i>club</i>

150
00:05:12,646 --> 00:05:15,524
since RJ and the students
have benefited so much from it.

151
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:21,946
Oh, this? I'm just--
I'm trying something new.

152
00:05:21,947 --> 00:05:24,281
Red is supposed to be
persuasive, okay?

153
00:05:24,282 --> 00:05:26,075
So, about the golf club,
I was thinking--

154
00:05:26,076 --> 00:05:27,618
Oh, uh, we will be
shutting that down

155
00:05:27,619 --> 00:05:29,328
after this school year,
no question.

156
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:31,580
Okay, what if
we <i>didn't</i> do that?

157
00:05:31,581 --> 00:05:33,415
What are you prepared
to give me?

158
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:35,584
Nothing.
No more bribes.

159
00:05:35,585 --> 00:05:36,794
Everything above water.

160
00:05:36,795 --> 00:05:38,754
So, I would give you
a golf club,

161
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:40,464
and you would give me...

162
00:05:40,465 --> 00:05:43,008
The satisfaction of knowing
you created a program

163
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:45,219
that helped
so many children.

164
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:46,845
Ava was so much better
at this.

165
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:49,473
Uh, look, the tax breaks
for a student club,

166
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:50,808
they don't move
the needle enough.

167
00:05:50,809 --> 00:05:52,184
Hold on.

168
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:53,769
This can be
a mutually beneficial deal.

169
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:56,564
If you designated a separate
community club for all ages,

170
00:05:56,565 --> 00:05:59,942
thus reclassifying under
the 501(c) nonprofit tax code...

171
00:05:59,943 --> 00:06:02,653
Go on.
I looked at the comps in
the area and I ran the numbers.

172
00:06:02,654 --> 00:06:04,029
With that tax savings,

173
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:07,241
you would net more than 5%
more revenue annually.

174
00:06:07,242 --> 00:06:09,994
So this would be
a <i>legal</i> bribe.

175
00:06:09,995 --> 00:06:11,203
Otherwise known
as a deal.

176
00:06:11,204 --> 00:06:13,122
I like the cut
of your jib, Eddie.

177
00:06:13,123 --> 00:06:15,082
Oh, and, by the way,
your shirt, it really--

178
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:16,292
Persuaded you?

179
00:06:16,293 --> 00:06:18,294
Made me want to switch
to State Farm.

180
00:06:18,295 --> 00:06:21,505
Consider burning that.
Okay, take care, now.

181
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:22,923
Alright,
Abbott Elementary.

182
00:06:22,924 --> 00:06:25,301
What is this new evidence
that has come to light?

183
00:06:25,302 --> 00:06:27,094
[ Sighs ]

184
00:06:27,095 --> 00:06:28,430
What new evidence?

185
00:06:30,432 --> 00:06:32,099
Oh, just a little thing
called the truth!

186
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:33,392
Ow.
Wow.

187
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:35,269
Ava had nothing to do
with taking bribes

188
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:37,396
from the golf course.

189
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:38,522
Because it was me.

190
00:06:38,523 --> 00:06:40,692
And me.

191
00:06:43,361 --> 00:06:45,946
I may or may not
have known about things

192
00:06:45,947 --> 00:06:47,948
that may or may not
have happened.

193
00:06:47,949 --> 00:06:51,327
Ava took the blame because it
would be harder on our students

194
00:06:51,328 --> 00:06:52,870
to replace their
day-to-day teachers,

195
00:06:52,871 --> 00:06:54,747
even if it was temporary.

196
00:06:54,748 --> 00:06:56,999
Isn't that the exact
kind of principal

197
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,376
we want leading
our schools?

198
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:01,337
Is this true?
Of course.

199
00:07:01,338 --> 00:07:02,880
Anyone can do what <i>I</i> do,

200
00:07:02,881 --> 00:07:07,635
but capable teachers like
J-Janine are irreplaceable.

201
00:07:07,636 --> 00:07:10,180
[ Indistinct conversation ]

202
00:07:11,723 --> 00:07:14,308
Well, it appears
that we have made a mistake.

203
00:07:14,309 --> 00:07:16,352
Oh!
Thank you
for your honesty

204
00:07:16,353 --> 00:07:18,187
and for setting
the record straight.

205
00:07:18,188 --> 00:07:20,939
So, per this new information,
as of Monday,

206
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:22,399
you're all suspended
for a week.

207
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,400
What?
Suspended?

208
00:07:23,401 --> 00:07:24,568
For a week?

209
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:25,944
Do you know how hard
it's gonna be

210
00:07:25,945 --> 00:07:27,529
to find subs
for this many teachers?

211
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:29,365
I do not, because
it's not my jurisdiction.

212
00:07:29,366 --> 00:07:31,617
Okay, I have a dependent
at the school

213
00:07:31,618 --> 00:07:34,203
that relies on me
being physically present.

214
00:07:34,204 --> 00:07:35,079
And what is
the child's name?

215
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,163
Sweet Cheeks.

216
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:37,331
Sw--

217
00:07:37,332 --> 00:07:38,666
It's a guinea pig.

218
00:07:38,667 --> 00:07:41,335
Well, Sweet Cheeks
is suspended, as well.

219
00:07:41,336 --> 00:07:43,629
Okay, but at least
Ava's back as principal.

220
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:44,880
Of course not.

221
00:07:44,881 --> 00:07:47,466
She's still fired
for lying to the board.

222
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:49,761
[ Sighs ]
Great plan, Janine.

223
00:07:52,389 --> 00:07:55,391
Um, yeah, just letting you know
that you will be having a sub

224
00:07:55,392 --> 00:07:56,850
or series of subs taking over
for me next week.

225
00:07:56,851 --> 00:07:58,185
What are you doing
for a whole week?

226
00:07:58,186 --> 00:07:59,728
Did you get in trouble?
No.

227
00:07:59,729 --> 00:08:02,022
I'm simply taking
a principled vacation

228
00:08:02,023 --> 00:08:03,482
in support
of Principal Coleman.

229
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:06,026
That's not a vacation, bro.
You got suspended.

230
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:07,820
Okay, uh...

231
00:08:07,821 --> 00:08:09,071
They suspended you
for trying

232
00:08:09,072 --> 00:08:10,656
to get Principal Coleman's
job back?

233
00:08:10,657 --> 00:08:12,241
Dang.
That's messed up.

234
00:08:12,242 --> 00:08:13,867
Yeah, we should
do something.

235
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:15,619
Yeah.
No, no.

236
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:18,247
Look, I-I appreciate
you guys so much,

237
00:08:18,248 --> 00:08:21,542
but this is not
your fight, okay?

238
00:08:21,543 --> 00:08:23,502
Alright, class,
Miss Teagues won't be here,

239
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:26,422
uh, next Monday, okay?

240
00:08:26,423 --> 00:08:29,717
Or Tuesday... or Wednesday
or Thursday or Friday.

241
00:08:29,718 --> 00:08:32,219
Together: No!

242
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:33,595
Yes, Lila.

243
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:35,055
How come?

244
00:08:35,056 --> 00:08:38,767
Miss Teagues will be
on a long, unpaid vacation.

245
00:08:38,768 --> 00:08:40,228
But you'll be back
for Earth Day?

246
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:43,814
I'm <i>not</i> gonna be back
for Earth Day.

247
00:08:43,815 --> 00:08:45,525
Oh, my God,
what did we do?

248
00:08:47,318 --> 00:08:49,778
You know, we did everything
we could to get Ava back,

249
00:08:49,779 --> 00:08:51,113
and she's still fired.

250
00:08:51,114 --> 00:08:53,073
You know, this is the first
and only time

251
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:56,535
I have been professionally
reprimanded in my entire career.

252
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:58,912
And I do not plan
to be a good sport about it.

253
00:08:58,913 --> 00:09:00,414
Same.

254
00:09:00,415 --> 00:09:02,082
I've only been suspended
in my nightmares.

255
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:03,876
And even then,
my dream self wakes up

256
00:09:03,877 --> 00:09:05,794
to a dream
where I'm not suspended.

257
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:08,213
Okay, it's-- it's a huge
bummer, alright?

258
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:09,923
But I'm not gonna lie.

259
00:09:09,924 --> 00:09:13,469
Gregory being principal is not
the worst thing in the world.

260
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:16,180
Well, I appreciate the praise,
but the job isn't mine.

261
00:09:16,181 --> 00:09:17,765
I'm gonna interview
for it,

262
00:09:17,766 --> 00:09:18,932
but they'll be interviewing
a lot of people for the role.

263
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:20,267
So it could be anybody?

264
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:22,686
Yeah, I heard
even Morton's interviewing.

265
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:24,146
I will riot!
Gregory: Agreed.

266
00:09:24,147 --> 00:09:25,272
I'll see you all later.

267
00:09:25,273 --> 00:09:27,065
I now have to go find
a bunch of subs

268
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:28,525
we definitely don't have
for next week.

269
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:30,402
Melissa: Oh, hell naw.

270
00:09:30,403 --> 00:09:34,406
We cannot allow some
rando principal or Morton...

271
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:36,658
[ Gags ]
...to come in here
and ruin our school.

272
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:38,285
Yeah, well, what are we
gonna do about it?

273
00:09:38,286 --> 00:09:39,870
Because we are all
out of options.

274
00:09:39,871 --> 00:09:41,705
No, no, no, no, no,
we just need to think

275
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:43,749
outside of the box
to bring Ava back, okay?

276
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,209
Come on,
let's brainstorm.

277
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:46,418
There are no bad ideas, okay?
Alright, come on.

278
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:48,587
I know a brother
who clones for the low.

279
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:51,424
We raise the clone,
teach her how to be a principal.

280
00:09:54,094 --> 00:09:55,177
Mm-hmm.
Let's keep brainstorming.

281
00:09:55,178 --> 00:09:56,470
- Okay, yeah.
- Yeah.

282
00:09:56,471 --> 00:09:58,472
Thank you both
for hopping on this Zoom.

283
00:09:58,473 --> 00:10:00,516
Um, Tariq, please tell me
that's a fake background.

284
00:10:00,517 --> 00:10:02,267
<i>Why would it be fake?</i>

285
00:10:02,268 --> 00:10:03,435
Okay.
[ <i>Toilet flushes</i> ]

286
00:10:03,436 --> 00:10:05,062
Would both of you
be able to help out

287
00:10:05,063 --> 00:10:06,814
in some classrooms
next week?

288
00:10:06,815 --> 00:10:08,440
A bunch of teachers
got suspended

289
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:10,067
trying to help Ava
get her job back.

290
00:10:10,068 --> 00:10:11,860
<i>Ooh. Okay,
here's the thing.</i>

291
00:10:11,861 --> 00:10:14,655
<i>Yes, but I could not help out
with math, English,</i>

292
00:10:14,656 --> 00:10:16,198
<i>history, or science.</i>

293
00:10:16,199 --> 00:10:18,450
<i>What the hell is wrong
with these district people?</i>

294
00:10:18,451 --> 00:10:20,953
<i>You know, they're gonna make
this bitch become that bitch.</i>

295
00:10:20,954 --> 00:10:22,538
<i>Mm-hmm, yes.</i>
Oh.

296
00:10:22,539 --> 00:10:23,789
<i>As a matter of fact, I'm coming
down there right now, bro.</i>

297
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,123
No, no, no, no,
unh-unh, no, no.

298
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:26,291
Sit down.
It's okay.

299
00:10:26,292 --> 00:10:28,043
I don't need you, um,
until Monday,

300
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:30,546
but I appreciate
the enthusiasm.

301
00:10:30,547 --> 00:10:33,757
<i>Okay, well, we're gonna be
down there for sure, brother.</i>

302
00:10:33,758 --> 00:10:35,217
Okay.
<i>Oh, yeah, you're gonna
see us real soon.</i>

303
00:10:35,218 --> 00:10:36,677
<i>Mm-hmm.
I'm getting sick of them.</i>

304
00:10:36,678 --> 00:10:38,220
[ Indistinct whispering ]
Janine: This can't be it.

305
00:10:38,221 --> 00:10:39,763
What haven't we
thought of yet?

306
00:10:39,764 --> 00:10:42,266
Squatter's rights.
This is our school now.
Ooh, yeah.

307
00:10:42,267 --> 00:10:44,434
Hey, Mrs. Howard, can I borrow
some of your markers

308
00:10:44,435 --> 00:10:46,436
from the classroom?
Sure, sweetheart.

309
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:47,688
Just put them back
when you're done.

310
00:10:47,689 --> 00:10:48,772
You know, this never
would have happened

311
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:50,274
if we were
a charter school.

312
00:10:50,275 --> 00:10:52,401
They're allowed to solicit
donations all they want.

313
00:10:52,402 --> 00:10:54,611
Oh, my God, Jacob,
you beautiful genius.

314
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:56,530
That's it.
We become a charter school.

315
00:10:56,531 --> 00:10:58,198
Just for a little bit,
and then we change back.

316
00:10:58,199 --> 00:10:59,408
Okay, how the hell
do we do that?

317
00:10:59,409 --> 00:11:01,577
One step
ahead of you.

318
00:11:01,578 --> 00:11:05,706
"How to become
a charter school."

319
00:11:05,707 --> 00:11:07,875
Make an account?
Never mind.

320
00:11:07,876 --> 00:11:09,543
Hey, Mr. C,
can I borrow this?

321
00:11:09,544 --> 00:11:10,794
Sure, bud.
All yours.

322
00:11:10,795 --> 00:11:11,962
Mr. Johnson: I got it.

323
00:11:11,963 --> 00:11:14,131
I'll interview for principal,
get the job.

324
00:11:14,132 --> 00:11:16,216
Then we'll need
a new janitor.

325
00:11:16,217 --> 00:11:17,634
Ava applies
for the position.

326
00:11:17,635 --> 00:11:19,052
And then...

327
00:11:19,053 --> 00:11:20,470
What are we trying
to do again?

328
00:11:20,471 --> 00:11:23,682
Oh, you know,
maybe it is just time

329
00:11:23,683 --> 00:11:26,226
that we accept the things
we cannot change.

330
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:28,145
[ Bangs table ]
I can't accept that.

331
00:11:28,146 --> 00:11:30,439
Okay, there might be
one thing.

332
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:31,899
What?
What?

333
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:33,775
It's the
Schemmenti Diversion.

334
00:11:33,776 --> 00:11:35,319
It's an old
family secret.

335
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:37,487
I'm gonna need a dozen
balaclava, a tray of baklava,

336
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:39,573
an ice cream truck,
and a boatload of zip ties,

337
00:11:39,574 --> 00:11:41,783
and the grace of God.

338
00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:42,784
We in?
Yeah.

339
00:11:42,785 --> 00:11:44,119
Jacob: Let's do it.

340
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:46,538
First we get him
into a clown wig.

341
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:48,457
I was up all night
trying to figure this out,

342
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:50,125
but I think we'll be able
to have all of our classes

343
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:51,210
covered while our teachers
are suspended.

344
00:11:52,587 --> 00:11:54,546
Look, I do wish Ava was here,

345
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:56,673
but getting to do
all of this problem-solving

346
00:11:56,674 --> 00:11:59,593
and decision-making
in support of the entire school

347
00:11:59,594 --> 00:12:02,387
is starting to make me remember

348
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:04,724
why I wanted to be principal
in the first place.

349
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:10,270
You want a high five?
I don't give those.

350
00:12:10,271 --> 00:12:12,272
By the way,
your paycheck arrived.

351
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:13,149
Oh.

352
00:12:17,612 --> 00:12:19,279
God damn!

353
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:21,615
Never seen a check
like that before, huh?

354
00:12:21,616 --> 00:12:24,159
No, I have not.

355
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:26,286
Okay, I picked up
the five dozen balloons.

356
00:12:26,287 --> 00:12:27,871
Did you pay in cash? 'Cause
we can't leave a paper trail.

357
00:12:27,872 --> 00:12:29,581
Why did I need to buy
88 gumballs?

358
00:12:29,582 --> 00:12:31,541
Janine, please tell me
you blew the bubble,

359
00:12:31,542 --> 00:12:33,168
'cause I'm not doing it
for you again.

360
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:36,171
Important thing, the oxygen tank
taps out after 30 minutes.

361
00:12:36,172 --> 00:12:37,464
Right.
Got it?

362
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:39,883
This just might work out.
Okay, let's do it.

363
00:12:39,884 --> 00:12:41,593
[ Students chanting
"Save our teachers!" ]

364
00:12:41,594 --> 00:12:43,136
- Okay.
- Is it recess?

365
00:12:43,137 --> 00:12:45,555
You all think your plan
is so clever?

366
00:12:45,556 --> 00:12:47,683
Guess what, smarties.
It's gonna backfire.

367
00:12:47,684 --> 00:12:49,309
Oh, my God,
there's a rat amongst us.

368
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:51,019
A walkout's not gonna
change our decision.

369
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:53,188
Wait, what?
Uh, a walkout?

370
00:12:53,189 --> 00:12:54,940
Brandon, what--
what is going on?

371
00:12:54,941 --> 00:12:56,400
We're protesting,
Mr. C.

372
00:12:56,401 --> 00:12:58,068
We can't let you guys
take that L.

373
00:12:58,069 --> 00:12:59,611
Melissa: Aww!

374
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:01,738
They're peacefully protesting.

375
00:13:01,739 --> 00:13:03,074
I'm just--

376
00:13:06,119 --> 00:13:09,204
Okay, I hear you,

377
00:13:09,205 --> 00:13:12,249
I see you,
and I respect you.

378
00:13:12,250 --> 00:13:14,084
But please do not walk out

379
00:13:14,085 --> 00:13:15,544
and make this the worst day
of my job.

380
00:13:15,545 --> 00:13:18,046
The district will be here
shortly to quell--

381
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:23,093
to <i>listen</i> to you
and your needs shortly.

382
00:13:23,094 --> 00:13:25,262
[ Students cheering ]

383
00:13:25,263 --> 00:13:27,097
Okay,
I'm gonna go call Ava.

384
00:13:27,098 --> 00:13:29,182
Barbara:
Alright, alright.

385
00:13:29,183 --> 00:13:31,351
Alright,
the clock is ticking.

386
00:13:31,352 --> 00:13:33,020
They have 29 minutes
of oxygen left.

387
00:13:33,021 --> 00:13:34,397
Uh, um...
We should get them.

388
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:40,527
We love how passionate
you all are about your school,

389
00:13:40,528 --> 00:13:42,320
which is why we thought
it would be a good idea

390
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:45,699
to have this forum, which
just so happens to coincide

391
00:13:45,700 --> 00:13:47,534
with you wanting to walk
out of the school.

392
00:13:47,535 --> 00:13:49,536
Rick:
We are here to listen.

393
00:13:49,537 --> 00:13:51,163
For 30 seconds
at a time.

394
00:13:51,164 --> 00:13:52,706
Well, thank you
for hearing us out.

395
00:13:52,707 --> 00:13:55,459
Um, if anyone would like to
speak, just stand up, I guess.

396
00:13:55,460 --> 00:13:57,794
Well said.
Next speaker.

397
00:13:57,795 --> 00:14:00,505
[ Voice breaking ] Ava and these
teachers are my closest friends.

398
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:01,757
Oh, not this again.

399
00:14:01,758 --> 00:14:03,091
I love them,

400
00:14:03,092 --> 00:14:04,593
and they challenge me
to be better every day.

401
00:14:04,594 --> 00:14:07,220
Really? Morton is the ace
up your sleeve?

402
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:08,805
Knew I should've
went to the club.

403
00:14:08,806 --> 00:14:10,474
Look,
the kids did it, okay?

404
00:14:10,475 --> 00:14:12,893
We had a slightly
more complicated plan,

405
00:14:12,894 --> 00:14:14,269
but I think this one
is better.

406
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:15,312
It's just
like I tell my wife.

407
00:14:15,313 --> 00:14:17,773
Sorry, my ex-ex-wife.

408
00:14:17,774 --> 00:14:19,274
Janine: Oh, my God.
I say, look--

409
00:14:19,275 --> 00:14:21,109
Okay, I think we got it, Morton.
Thanks.

410
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:23,487
Our teachers do everything.
What do y'all do?

411
00:14:23,488 --> 00:14:25,489
[ Students shouting ]

412
00:14:25,490 --> 00:14:27,449
Aren't y'all the ones that took
our archery equipment?

413
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:29,159
How am I supposed to become
the next Hawkeye?

414
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:31,286
Okay, please, please,
one at a time.

415
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:32,621
I was having a hard time,

416
00:14:32,622 --> 00:14:34,539
but these teachers
and Principal Coleman

417
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:36,541
stepped up when I thought
no one else cared.

418
00:14:36,542 --> 00:14:39,127
Without them,
I don't know where I would be.

419
00:14:39,128 --> 00:14:40,712
RJ speaking
at a rally?

420
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:42,005
We have come so far.
Yeah.

421
00:14:42,006 --> 00:14:44,299
So moving, right?

422
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:46,718
Well, the good news,
kiddos,

423
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:50,764
is that your teachers will be
back in five business days,

424
00:14:50,765 --> 00:14:54,143
and we are working very hard
to find you a new principal.

425
00:14:55,603 --> 00:14:57,354
Excuse me.
Have you decided

426
00:14:57,355 --> 00:14:59,189
how much that new principal
will be making?

427
00:14:59,190 --> 00:15:02,234
Do you have any idea
how much property damage

428
00:15:02,235 --> 00:15:04,361
can be accomplished
in five business days?

429
00:15:04,362 --> 00:15:05,821
Really?
Really?

430
00:15:05,822 --> 00:15:07,614
Nothing that you have heard
from these students

431
00:15:07,615 --> 00:15:09,574
or the faculty
matter to you?

432
00:15:09,575 --> 00:15:10,992
No.

433
00:15:10,993 --> 00:15:14,287
So if everyone
is done feeling heard...

434
00:15:14,288 --> 00:15:15,455
[ Murmuring ]

435
00:15:15,456 --> 00:15:17,124
Good.
Great, okay.

436
00:15:17,125 --> 00:15:18,917
Ava:
Janine, we lost.

437
00:15:18,918 --> 00:15:21,419
It happens.
To you all the time.

438
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:23,255
No, no, no, no, no.
Maybe if we, um...

439
00:15:23,256 --> 00:15:24,589
I think we--
we can probably--

440
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:27,300
Janine, it's over.

441
00:15:27,301 --> 00:15:29,469
[ Door opens ]
Tariq: On your left.

442
00:15:29,470 --> 00:15:32,013
[ Murmuring ]

443
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:35,392
My bad. I meant my left.
Uh, y'all's right.

444
00:15:35,393 --> 00:15:38,603
As the PTA,
we will not stand by

445
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:40,897
while y'all are hurting
our children's education

446
00:15:40,898 --> 00:15:42,357
with this nonsense.

447
00:15:42,358 --> 00:15:44,776
You can say that again.

448
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:47,737
As the B.L.A.C.K.S.,
we've seen firsthand

449
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:51,658
how Miss Coleman has transformed
this rundown elementary school

450
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:53,910
into an unpredictable
music venue.

451
00:15:53,911 --> 00:15:55,829
And I speak
for the local businesses

452
00:15:55,830 --> 00:15:58,957
when I say that we have seen
the positive changes

453
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:00,375
that this school
and its leadership

454
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:03,253
has contributed
to this community.

455
00:16:03,254 --> 00:16:06,173
They supported us
during the SEPTA strike,

456
00:16:06,174 --> 00:16:07,549
so we are here
to support them!

457
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:09,801
[ Cheering ]

458
00:16:09,802 --> 00:16:15,432
Perhaps this whole issue can
be put to bed by a white savior.

459
00:16:15,433 --> 00:16:18,977
Well, uh, as someone who
has bribed thousands of people

460
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:21,396
across this fair city,
this was the only place

461
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:23,607
that those bribes
benefited children

462
00:16:23,608 --> 00:16:25,692
and not corrupt officials.

463
00:16:25,693 --> 00:16:27,444
- He's not wrong.
- Okay.

464
00:16:27,445 --> 00:16:29,487
Oh, my gosh, guys, the community
is coming together,

465
00:16:29,488 --> 00:16:31,364
and we didn't even
have to trick them.

466
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:32,824
Good afternoon.

467
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:35,577
How many damn doors
do we have in this gym?

468
00:16:35,578 --> 00:16:37,996
Wasn't Crystal the one that
ratted us out to the district?

469
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:39,789
Yup. She must be here
to finish the job.

470
00:16:39,790 --> 00:16:42,417
Mm, just when we almost
had the board on our side.

471
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:44,711
Soror.

472
00:16:44,712 --> 00:16:46,630
- Boar-ord.
- Oh, no.

473
00:16:46,631 --> 00:16:48,715
Although I've had
my differences in the past

474
00:16:48,716 --> 00:16:51,051
with Principal Coleman...
Ava: You don't say.

475
00:16:51,052 --> 00:16:53,136
You're my number-one hater,
and I have a lot.

476
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:56,723
[ Sighs ] Myself and these
other principals know

477
00:16:56,724 --> 00:16:59,684
that no one fights harder
for their school than Ava

478
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:01,102
and these educators.

479
00:17:01,103 --> 00:17:02,979
Any school in this district

480
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:05,273
would be lucky
to have these teachers

481
00:17:05,274 --> 00:17:07,984
and a principal like Ava.

482
00:17:07,985 --> 00:17:09,736
And if you
think differently,

483
00:17:09,737 --> 00:17:12,822
then you don't know what's
best for your own district.

484
00:17:12,823 --> 00:17:14,824
[ Cheers and applause ]

485
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:17,035
Bring them back!

486
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:20,497
All: Bring them back!
Bring them back!

487
00:17:20,498 --> 00:17:21,998
Stop the chant!

488
00:17:21,999 --> 00:17:25,919
So, after hearing the
community's thoughtful thoughts,

489
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:28,421
we have decided
we have no choice

490
00:17:28,422 --> 00:17:31,675
but to go forward
with <i>our</i> original plan,

491
00:17:31,676 --> 00:17:36,388
which was to reinstate Ava
and her band of teachers.

492
00:17:36,389 --> 00:17:38,266
[ Cheers and applause ]

493
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:45,814
[ <i>Up-tempo music plays</i> ]
And slide...

494
00:17:45,815 --> 00:17:47,607
Ooh, they tried it,

495
00:17:47,608 --> 00:17:51,403
but my record, like my spirit,
remains unsullied.

496
00:17:51,404 --> 00:17:53,822
Uh-huh. Now, when are all these
people gonna go home?

497
00:17:53,823 --> 00:17:56,324
I don't know, but I have
an ice cream truck to return

498
00:17:56,325 --> 00:17:58,618
and a bunch of baklava
to eat.

499
00:17:58,619 --> 00:18:02,038
I wanted to thank you guys
for seeing this through.

500
00:18:02,039 --> 00:18:03,331
It really means a lot
to me.

501
00:18:03,332 --> 00:18:05,083
You're welcome.
It was worth it.

502
00:18:05,084 --> 00:18:07,752
Agreed. You, ma'am,
are worth the sacrifice.

503
00:18:07,753 --> 00:18:10,505
Mm-hmm.
I really am, aren't I?

504
00:18:10,506 --> 00:18:13,258
Like, if it wasn't for
how good and wonderful

505
00:18:13,259 --> 00:18:16,303
and impactful I am,
you'd have nothing to fight for.

506
00:18:16,304 --> 00:18:18,054
So I guess I got to
thank myself, too.

507
00:18:18,055 --> 00:18:20,807
Yeah.
There it is.

508
00:18:20,808 --> 00:18:24,144
Don't you think we ought to nip
this line dancing in the bud?

509
00:18:24,145 --> 00:18:25,895
Yeah, Jacob, get over there
and start dancing.

510
00:18:25,896 --> 00:18:27,439
That'll let the air
out of their tires.

511
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:29,816
Uh, looks like Miles
already has that covered.

512
00:18:29,817 --> 00:18:32,402
Barbara: Can't unsee it.
I can't unsee it.
Wow.

513
00:18:32,403 --> 00:18:33,820
Goodness.
Good night.

514
00:18:33,821 --> 00:18:35,613
Oh, also,
my internal clock

515
00:18:35,614 --> 00:18:37,198
has gotten used to
sleeping in till 10:00,

516
00:18:37,199 --> 00:18:40,493
so I'll be late
until I can reset that.

517
00:18:40,494 --> 00:18:42,871
Ooh, it is good
to have you back, friend.

518
00:18:42,872 --> 00:18:43,955
What's that?

519
00:18:43,956 --> 00:18:45,291
I mean
Principal Coleman.

520
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:51,129
Ava, congratulations.

521
00:18:51,130 --> 00:18:53,173
I'm glad to see
this all worked out.

522
00:18:53,174 --> 00:18:54,883
Well, you sure have
a lot of time

523
00:18:54,884 --> 00:18:56,384
to keep popping up
at this school.

524
00:18:56,385 --> 00:18:59,220
I'm just happy
to see you got a second chance.

525
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:01,514
Yeah, but see,
I got a second chance

526
00:19:01,515 --> 00:19:03,808
because I was actually good
at my first chance.

527
00:19:03,809 --> 00:19:05,019
Fair enough.

528
00:19:08,022 --> 00:19:10,857
I hope you know that...

529
00:19:10,858 --> 00:19:13,610
I'm proud of you.

530
00:19:13,611 --> 00:19:16,613
Even if I wasn't
always there.

531
00:19:16,614 --> 00:19:18,990
Thank you.

532
00:19:18,991 --> 00:19:21,826
I'm around
if you need anything.

533
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:23,244
What, for, like,
a haircut?

534
00:19:23,245 --> 00:19:24,954
Can you do a bob?
No.

535
00:19:24,955 --> 00:19:27,374
[ Chuckles ]

536
00:19:27,375 --> 00:19:29,626
I just mean...

537
00:19:29,627 --> 00:19:31,545
anything.

538
00:19:37,927 --> 00:19:39,803
[ Chuckles ] The power's
addicting, isn't it?

539
00:19:39,804 --> 00:19:41,054
I was just keeping it warm
for you.

540
00:19:41,055 --> 00:19:42,389
Ew.

541
00:19:42,390 --> 00:19:43,556
Now, what is that?

542
00:19:43,557 --> 00:19:45,558
Uh, lumbar support
for your lower back.

543
00:19:45,559 --> 00:19:46,643
You can keep it
if you want.

544
00:19:46,644 --> 00:19:47,936
Get a core.
Do a sit-up.

545
00:19:47,937 --> 00:19:49,938
I don't need that.

546
00:19:49,939 --> 00:19:51,731
I did want to say,

547
00:19:51,732 --> 00:19:54,192
thanks for holding down
the place while I was gone.

548
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:56,486
I heard you did
a great job.

549
00:19:56,487 --> 00:19:58,697
Thank you.
I enjoyed it.

550
00:19:58,698 --> 00:20:01,658
I can tell. You practically
moved into the place.

551
00:20:01,659 --> 00:20:03,911
Well, I'll, um,
leave you to it.

552
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:14,504
Well, Dia,
looks like this is it.

553
00:20:14,505 --> 00:20:15,964
You got fired, too?

554
00:20:15,965 --> 00:20:17,424
N-No.
I-I'm just--

555
00:20:17,425 --> 00:20:19,467
Then what do you want
a tearful goodbye for?

556
00:20:19,468 --> 00:20:20,677
Y'all deserve
each other.

557
00:20:20,678 --> 00:20:22,179
See you next week.

558
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:29,769
Very good.
I'm here.

559
00:20:29,770 --> 00:20:31,521
Why?

560
00:20:31,522 --> 00:20:33,481
Well, Greg said
that y'all needed some teachers,

561
00:20:33,482 --> 00:20:35,650
so here I am.

562
00:20:35,651 --> 00:20:38,194
Yeah, but that was only for
if we were suspended,

563
00:20:38,195 --> 00:20:39,195
which we were not.

564
00:20:39,196 --> 00:20:42,031
But you were there.

565
00:20:42,032 --> 00:20:44,534
Ohh.

566
00:20:44,535 --> 00:20:46,369
Yeah, so I was actually
kind of looking forward

567
00:20:46,370 --> 00:20:48,163
to having
some time off.

568
00:20:48,164 --> 00:20:51,791
And secretly, I would have
loved sitting at home

569
00:20:51,792 --> 00:20:54,419
catching up
on the Kate Hudson show.

570
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:58,631
Oh, I just love it when they
come dancing down the hallway.
Jennifer.

571
00:20:58,632 --> 00:21:01,259
So we figured, you know,
since Tariq's here, hey...

572
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:03,219
Alright, y'all,
my name is Tariq,

573
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:05,388
but you can call me
Mr. Coach Temple.

574
00:21:05,389 --> 00:21:06,598
I'm gonna be real up front
with y'all.

575
00:21:06,599 --> 00:21:08,016
I don't remember nothing
that I learned

576
00:21:08,017 --> 00:21:09,517
before the age of 12, okay?

577
00:21:09,518 --> 00:21:12,228
So I need somebody here
to tell me

578
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:14,898
how to craft a text message
to my landlord

579
00:21:14,899 --> 00:21:16,149
asking for a rent reduction.

580
00:21:16,150 --> 00:21:17,860
Real quick with the hands.
Come on.

581
00:21:20,321 --> 00:21:23,365
Don't hurt yourself.
Where they at?

